    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "<b>What is the NNO?</b>\r\nNNO stands for Noord Nederlands Concert. Despite
    being the orchestra of the North, we tour very regularly to other venues around
    the country, such as the Concertgebouw in Amsterdam, Tivoli Vredenburg in Utrecht
    and the Lowlands Festival. We can also be heard on radio, TV and (live)streams.
    \n\nIn recent years, many young talented musicians have been recruited. The NNO
    consists of around 70 musicians with 14 different nationalities, who together
    perform symphonic music at more than 100 concerts per season.\r\nYou'll find
    us in concert halls, outdoor venues, at festivals and school performances. For
    example, during the Pieter Roelf Youth Concerts where we introduce thousands
    of primary school pupils to classical music.\r\nThe NNO works closely with various
    other arts institutions, the Prince Claus Conservatoire in Groningen, the conservatoires
    in Amsterdam and The Hague, and the Nederlandse Reisopera.\r\n\r\n<b>Noord Nederlands
    Concert Choir</b>\r\nThe choir consists of a selection of the best amateur singers
    from the North of the Netherlands and performs choral works, often with a large
    ensemble and a higher level of difficulty. The NNCK is a project choir that performs
    exclusively alongside the NNO, a professional Dutch symphony orchestra.\r\nThe
    programming, artistic direction and quality standards that each singer must meet
    are determined by the NNO. Rehearsals and performances take place on a project
    basis. Think of the Matth\xE4us Passion in virtually all major concert halls
    in the North, as well as a performance at the Lowlands festival in Biddinghuizen.\r\n\r\n<i>For
    more than 30 years the permanent choir of the Noord Nederlands Orchestra</i>\r\nThe
    NNCK was founded in 1991 by the NNO out of a need for a strong choir of its own.
    This makes the NNO unique within the Dutch orchestra landscape. The NNCK performs
    exclusively in symphonic works for choir and orchestra by the NNO, three to four
    times per season. The choir numbers around one hundred vocalists, selected from
    the finest choral singers in the North.\r\n\r\n<b>The people behind the scenes</b>\r\nHundreds
    of people work at the NNO, spread across many different roles. We have dozens
    to nearly a hundred people performing in the orchestras themselves \u2014 whether
    it's the violinist at the front or the saxophone at the back. In addition, the
    NNO has 5 top conductors who effectively lead the entire orchestra."
